name: lnav_INCLUDES_WITH_SYSTEM
code: option(lnav_INCLUDES_WITH_SYSTEM "Use SYSTEM modifier for lnav's includes, disabling warnings" ON)

name: lnav_LIBS
code: set(lnav_LIBS CURL::libcurl SQLite::SQLite3 BZip2::BZip2 ncurses::libcurses pcre::libpcre readline::readline LibArchive::LibArchive ZLIB::ZLIB)

name: lnav_INSTALL_CMAKEDIR
code: set(lnav_INSTALL_CMAKEDIR "${CMAKE_INSTALL_DATADIR}/${package}" CACHE PATH "CMake package config location relative to the install prefix")

name: BUILD_MCSS_DOCS
code: option(BUILD_MCSS_DOCS "Build documentation using Doxygen and m.css" OFF)

name: DOXYGEN_OUTPUT_DIRECTORY
code: set(DOXYGEN_OUTPUT_DIRECTORY "${PROJECT_BINARY_DIR}/docs" CACHE PATH "Path for the generated Doxygen documentation")

name: docs
code: add_custom_target(docs COMMAND "${CMAKE_COMMAND}" -E remove_directory "${DOXYGEN_OUTPUT_DIRECTORY}/html" "${DOXYGEN_OUTPUT_DIRECTORY}/xml" COMMAND "${Python3_EXECUTABLE}" "${mcss_script}" "${config}" COMMENT "Building documentation using Doxygen and m.css" WORKING_DIRECTORY "${working_dir}" VERBATIM)

name: ENABLE_COVERAGE
code: option(ENABLE_COVERAGE "Enable coverage support separate from CTest's" OFF)

name: COVERAGE_TRACE_COMMAND
code: set(COVERAGE_TRACE_COMMAND lcov -c -q -o "${PROJECT_BINARY_DIR}/coverage.info" -d "${PROJECT_BINARY_DIR}" --include "${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR}/*" CACHE STRING "; separated command to generate a trace for the 'coverage' target")

name: COVERAGE_HTML_COMMAND
code: set(COVERAGE_HTML_COMMAND genhtml --legend -f -q "${PROJECT_BINARY_DIR}/coverage.info" -p "${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR}" -o "${PROJECT_BINARY_DIR}/coverage_html" CACHE STRING "; separated command to generate an HTML report for the 'coverage' target")

name: coverage
code: add_custom_target(coverage COMMAND ${COVERAGE_TRACE_COMMAND} COMMAND ${COVERAGE_HTML_COMMAND} COMMENT "Generating coverage report" VERBATIM)

name: FORMAT_PATTERNS
code: set(FORMAT_PATTERNS src/*.cc src/*.hh test/*.cc test/*.hh CACHE STRING "; separated patterns relative to the project source dir to format")

name: FORMAT_COMMAND
code: set(FORMAT_COMMAND clang-format CACHE STRING "Formatter to use")

name: format-check
code: add_custom_target(format-check COMMAND "${CMAKE_COMMAND}" -D "FORMAT_COMMAND=${FORMAT_COMMAND}" -D "PATTERNS=${FORMAT_PATTERNS}" -P "${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR}/cmake/lint.cmake" WORKING_DIRECTORY "${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR}" COMMENT "Linting the code" VERBATIM)

name: format-fix
code: add_custom_target(format-fix COMMAND "${CMAKE_COMMAND}" -D "FORMAT_COMMAND=${FORMAT_COMMAND}" -D "PATTERNS=${FORMAT_PATTERNS}" -D FIX=YES -P "${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR}/cmake/lint.cmake" WORKING_DIRECTORY "${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR}" COMMENT "Fixing the code" VERBATIM)

name: SPELL_COMMAND
code: set(SPELL_COMMAND codespell CACHE STRING "Spell checker to use")

name: spell-check
code: add_custom_target(spell-check COMMAND "${CMAKE_COMMAND}" -D "SPELL_COMMAND=${SPELL_COMMAND}" -P "${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR}/cmake/spell.cmake" WORKING_DIRECTORY "${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR}" COMMENT "Checking spelling" VERBATIM)

name: spell-fix
code: add_custom_target(spell-fix COMMAND "${CMAKE_COMMAND}" -D "SPELL_COMMAND=${SPELL_COMMAND}" -D FIX=YES -P "${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR}/cmake/spell.cmake" WORKING_DIRECTORY "${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR}" COMMENT "Fixing spelling errors" VERBATIM)
